entually develop.\n&gt; They all lead to the same thing - li=\r\nberation - in the end, but the\n&gt; trajectory is different.\n&gt;\n&gt; These four ba=\r\nsic paths constitute what are known as karma yoga\n&gt; (communion through acti=\r\non), jnana yoga (communion through wisdom),\n&gt; bhakti yoga (communion throug=\r\nh devotion) and raja yoga (communion\n&gt; through [self-]control). However, th=\r\nere are many sub-paths.\n&gt;\n&gt; Basically, different higher beings can increase=\r\n a different fine quality\n&gt; inside one, which is conducive to liberation. T=\r\nhe trajectory is\n&gt; different with each deity.\n&gt;\n&gt; * * *\n&gt;\n&gt; TOO MUNDANE?\n&gt;\n=\r\n&gt; The higher being I worshipped is supposed to increase control and\n&gt; maste=\r\nry over others. While I did the sadhana in the last few months, I\n&gt; wondere=\r\nd how *that* can lead to liberation. After all, control and\n&gt; mastery over =\r\nothers sounded too *mundane* to me to have anything to do\n&gt; with liberation=\r\n. But a simple realization came towards the end of the\n&gt; sadhana.\n&gt;\n&gt; * * *=\r\n\n&gt;\n&gt; CONTROL & FRICTION\n&gt;\n&gt; Whether A is attracted to B or B is attracted t=\r\no A, the bottomline is\n&gt; that objects A and B come together. The ability to=\r\n attract others also\n&gt; means to come together with them.\n&gt;\n&gt; One is unhappy=\r\n with others and thinks of controlling them, when one&#39;s\n&gt; own agenda is mis=\r\n-aligned with their agenda. The friction between the\n&gt; agendas is the basis=\r\n for the entire dynamics of likes, dislikes,\n&gt; frustrations etc. Control of=\r\n that friction comes when the agendas are\n&gt; nicely aligned!\n&gt;\n&gt; Ability to =\r\ncontrol the agenda pursued by someone else has limited use,\n&gt; scope and lif=\r\netime. Such an ability can work only with a limited set of\n&gt; people or a li=\r\nmited amount of time. This is like pumping rainwater from\n&gt; the fields surr=\r\nounding a hill to the top of the hill. It requires a lot\n&gt; of energy that i=\r\ns proportional to the area of the field and the amount\n&gt; of rainwater.\n&gt;\n&gt; =\r\nThe best way to avoid the friction, with ALL beings of the cosmos, is to\n&gt; =\r\neliminate one&#39;s own agenda! This is like removing the hill from the\n&gt; middl=\r\ne of the field, in the above analogy.\n&gt;\n&gt; If one has no agenda whatsoever, =\r\nthen there is no friction with anyone&#39;s\n&gt; agenda. There is no reason to lik=\r\ne or dislike anyone or find fault with\n&gt; or admire anyone. One can just obs=\r\nerve others. Because one has no\n&gt; agenda, one can identify with the agendas=\r\n of others and relate to them\n&gt; completely. One can then put oneself comple=\r\ntely in the shoes of others\n&gt; and feel their pleasures, pains etc.\n&gt;\n&gt; When=\r\n one has an agenda and another has another agenda, then there is\n&gt; friction=\r\n and one feels a need to &quot;control&quot; and remove friction. But,\n&gt; when one has=\r\n no agenda and another has an agenda, then there is no\n&gt; friction. One can =\r\nthen completely &quot;understand&quot; the perspective of the\n&gt; other (because there =\r\nis no friction from one&#39;s own agenda stopping one\n&gt; from doing so!). What b=\r\netter mastery and control can one have on someone\n&gt; else than be able to un=\r\nderstand that person completely?!\n&gt;\n&gt; Though what I described above is the =\r\nend, one path to that end is to\n&gt; identify one&#39;s own agenda/conditioning th=\r\nat is resulting in friction,\n&gt; whenever one is not happy with someone, and =\r\ntry to remove/suppress that\n&gt; conditioning. One can first try this with a f=\r\new people (e.g. spouse).\n&gt;\n&gt; * * *\n&gt;\n&gt; LOVE & COMPASSION FOR ALL\n&gt;\n&gt; Bottom=\r\nline is this: Control and mastery over others does not mean making\n&gt; them t=\r\nhink and behave in tune with the agenda of one&#39;s own limited\n&gt; conditioning=\r\n. Instead, it means overcoming&#39;s one&#39;s own agendas and being\n&gt; able to put =\r\noneself in the shoes of anybody and understand and feel each\n&gt; of their fee=\r\nlings and emotions. It means unconditional love and\n&gt; compassion for all.\n&gt;=\r\n\n&gt; * * *\n&gt;\n&gt; LOOKING DOWN ON OTHERS\n&gt;\n&gt; When one is doing some sadhana, one=\r\n of the stages one goes through may\n&gt; be to feel proud of one&#39;s sadhana, lo=\r\nok at some others doing such a\n&gt; sadhana favorably or with admiration and l=\r\nook down on others who are not\n&gt; doing much sadhana (or doing a different s=\r\nadhana!) and pursuing mundane\n&gt; things. This may be a natural tendency, but=\r\n realize that this is a work\n&gt; of the limited personality or ego.\n&gt;\n&gt; One h=\r\nas to overcome that tendency, for looking down on others will\n&gt; eventually =\r\nblock one.\n&gt;\n&gt; * * *\n&gt;\n&gt; LOVING THE DIVINE MOTHER\n&gt;\n&gt; People talk of loving=\r\n the Divine Mother. The personality of Divine\n&gt; Mother is beyond one&#39;s perc=\r\neption. How can one really love Her then?\n&gt;\n&gt; One may do tremendous sadhana=\r\n and get tremendous visions and think that\n&gt; one has grasped the personalit=\r\ny of Divine Mother, but what one perceives\n&gt; is merely what one&#39;s condition=\r\ning fancies and is capable of grasping!\n&gt; The complete personality of Divin=\r\ne Mother is beyond anybody&#39;s\n&gt; perception.\n&gt;\n&gt; However, Divine Mother does =\r\nmanifest in a perceptible way as the cosmos.\n&gt; Every being in the cosmos is=\r\n a limited manifestation of Her. Being able\n&gt; to love every being is the FI=\r\nRST step in truly loving the Divine Mother.\n&gt;\n&gt; Loving someone because they=\r\n are doing some good work (as we see it!) or\n&gt; because they have something =\r\nwe need (as we see it!) etc, is *egoistic*\n&gt; loving. Such love is *conditio=\r\nned* by the agendas of a limited ego. Such\n&gt; love cannot extend to entire c=\r\nosmos and permanently. The only love that\n&gt; can extend to entire cosmos and=\r\n be permanent is unconditional love of\n&gt; all beings.\n&gt;\n&gt; That comes only wh=\r\nen one has no agenda and no expectations from anyone.\n&gt;\n&gt; Best regards,\n&gt; N=\r\narasimha\n&gt; ----------------------------------------------------------\n&gt; Fre=\r\ne Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyotish Writings,\n&gt; &quot;Do It Yourse=\r\nlf&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam and Pitri Tarpana:\n&gt; http://www.VedicAst=\r\nrologer.org\n&gt; Films that make a difference: http://SaraswatiFilms.org\n&gt; Spi=\r\nrituality: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom\n&gt; Jyotish writings: h=\r\nttp://groups.yahoo.com/group/JyotishWritings\n&gt; Twitter ID: @homam108\n&gt; ----=\r\n------------------------------------------------------\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;   \n&gt;\n\r\n--e89a8ff25008b2858504bad1b012\r\nContent-Type: text/html; charset=UTF-8\r\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable\r\n\r\n&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000099&quot;&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;font face=3D&quot;verdana,sans-serif&quot;&gt;Hare Ramakr=\r\nishna!&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font class=3D&quot;Apple-style-span&quot; color=3D&quot;#=\r\n000099&quot; face=3D&quot;verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;Let us imagine, how Shri Ramana-Mahars=\r\nhi or Ramakrishna-Pramahamsa or Swami Sivananda would have responded if the=\r\ny have been put up with the hypothetical friends described by Aswin Kumar. =\r\nWouldn&#39;t it give us a clue?&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000099&quot;&gt;=\r\n&lt;font&gt;&lt;font face=3D&quot;verdana,sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br clear=3D&quot;all&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/f=\r\nont&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font face=3D&quot;&#39;trebuchet ms&#39;, sans-serif&quot; color=3D&quot;#009900&quot;&gt;=\r\nAum Tat Sat!&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font class=3D&quot;Apple-style-span&quot; c