ol of that friction comes whe=\r\nn the agendas are &lt;br&gt;\nnicely aligned!&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nAbility to control the agen=\r\nda pursued by someone else has limited use, &lt;br&gt;\nscope and lifetime. Such a=\r\nn ability can work only with a limited set of &lt;br&gt;\npeople or a limited amou=\r\nnt of time. This is like pumping rainwater from &lt;br&gt;\nthe fields surrounding=\r\n a hill to the top of the hill. It requires a lot &lt;br&gt;\nof energy that is pr=\r\noportional to the area of the field and the amount &lt;br&gt;\nof rainwater.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;=\r\nbr&gt;\nThe best way to avoid the friction, with ALL beings of the cosmos, is t=\r\no &lt;br&gt;\neliminate one&#39;s own agenda! This is like removing the hill from =\r\nthe &lt;br&gt;\nmiddle of the field, in the above analogy.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nIf one has no =\r\nagenda whatsoever, then there is no friction with anyone&#39;s &lt;br&gt;\nagenda.=\r\n There is no reason to like or dislike anyone or find fault with &lt;br&gt;\nor ad=\r\nmire anyone. One can just observe others. Because one has no &lt;br&gt;\nagenda, o=\r\nne can identify with the agendas of others and relate to them &lt;br&gt;\ncomplete=\r\nly. One can then put oneself completely in the shoes of others &lt;br&gt;\nand fee=\r\nl their pleasures, pains etc.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nWhen one has an agenda and another h=\r\nas another agenda, then there is &lt;br&gt;\nfriction and one feels a need to &quo=\r\nt;control&quot; and remove friction. But, &lt;br&gt;\nwhen one has no agenda and a=\r\nnother has an agenda, then there is no &lt;br&gt;\nfriction. One can then complete=\r\nly &quot;understand&quot; the perspective of the &lt;br&gt;\nother (because there =\r\nis no friction from one&#39;s own agenda stopping one &lt;br&gt;\nfrom doing so!).=\r\n What better mastery and control can one have on someone &lt;br&gt;\nelse than be =\r\nable to understand that person completely?!&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nThough what I describe=\r\nd above is the end, one path to that end is to &lt;br&gt;\nidentify one&#39;s own =\r\nagenda/conditioning that is resulting in friction, &lt;br&gt;\nwhenever one is not=\r\n happy with someone, and try to remove/suppress that &lt;br&gt;\nconditioning. One=\r\n can first try this with a few people (e.g. spouse).&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n*        *   =\r\n     *&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nLOVE &amp; COMPASSION FOR ALL&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nBottomline is this: =\r\nControl and mastery over others does not mean making &lt;br&gt;\nthem think and be=\r\nhave in tune with the agenda of one&#39;s own limited &lt;br&gt;\nconditioning. In=\r\nstead, it means overcoming&#39;s one&#39;s own agendas and being &lt;br&gt;\nable =\r\nto put oneself in the shoes of anybody and understand and feel each &lt;br&gt;\nof=\r\n their feelings and emotions. It means unconditional love and &lt;br&gt;\ncompassi=\r\non for all.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n*        *        *&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nLOOKING DOWN ON OTHERS&lt;br=\r\n&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nWhen one is doing some sadhana, one of the stages one goes through m=\r\nay &lt;br&gt;\nbe to feel proud of one&#39;s sadhana, look at some others doing su=\r\nch a &lt;br&gt;\nsadhana favorably or with admiration and look down on others who =\r\nare not &lt;br&gt;\ndoing much sadhana (or doing a different sadhana!) and pursuin=\r\ng mundane &lt;br&gt;\nthings. This may be a natural tendency, but realize that thi=\r\ns is a work &lt;br&gt;\nof the limited personality or ego.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nOne has to ove=\r\nrcome that tendency, for looking down on others will &lt;br&gt;\neventually block =\r\none.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n*        *        *&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nLOVING THE DIVINE MOTHER&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br=\r\n&gt;\nPeople talk of loving the Divine Mother. The personality of Divine &lt;br&gt;\nM=\r\nother is beyond one&#39;s perception. How can one really love Her then?&lt;br&gt;=\r\n\n&lt;br&gt;\nOne may do tremendous sadhana and get tremendous visions and think th=\r\nat &lt;br&gt;\none has grasped the personality of Divine Mother, but what one perc=\r\neives &lt;br&gt;\nis merely what one&#39;s conditioning fancies and is capable of =\r\ngrasping! &lt;br&gt;\nThe complete personality of Divine Mother is beyond anybody&=\r\n#39;s &lt;br&gt;\nperception.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nHowever, Divine Mother does manifest in a p=\r\nerceptible way as the cosmos. &lt;br&gt;\nEvery being in the cosmos is a limited m=\r\nanifestation of Her. Being able &lt;br&gt;\nto love every being is the FIRST step =\r\nin truly loving the Divine Mother.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nLoving someone because they are=\r\n doing some good work (as we see it!) or &lt;br&gt;\nbecause they have something w=\r\ne need (as we see it!) etc, is *egoistic* &lt;br&gt;\nloving. Such love is *condit=\r\nioned* by the agendas of a limited ego. Such &lt;br&gt;\nlove cannot extend to ent=\r\nire cosmos and permanently. The only love that &lt;br&gt;\ncan extend to entire co=\r\nsmos and be permanent is unconditional love of &lt;br&gt;\nall beings.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nTh=\r\nat comes only when one has no agenda and no expectations from anyone.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;=\r\nbr&gt;\nBest regards,&lt;br&gt;\nNarasimha&lt;br&gt;\n---------------------------------------=\r\n-------------------&lt;br&gt;\n   Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyo=\r\ntish Writings,&lt;br&gt;\n&quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homa=\r\nm and Pitri Tarpana:&lt;br&gt;\n                   &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; href=3D&quot;htt=\r\np://www.VedicAstrologer.org&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.VedicAstrologer.o=\r\nrg&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n      Films that make a difference: &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; href=3D&quot;=\r\nhttp://SaraswatiFilms.org&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://SaraswatiFilms.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;=\r\nbr&gt;\n      Spirituality: &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; href=3D&quot;http://groups.yahoo.com=\r\n/group/vedic-wisdom&